text:
Should she need letters written, let them ask of me;
At dawn, my pen on ear for all the world to see,
Prepared for her command, I left my home.

The very ones from whom I sought some praise for pain,
Proved even more afflicted by a cruel disdain;
They bore more wounds from tyranny's sharp sword.

In love, there is no space 'twixt life and death's dark art;
I live by looking at the one who holds my heart—
That cruel beloved for whom my soul would die.
